# TCP/IP Model (Cybersecurity)

The TCP/IP model is the practical version of networking used on the internet.  
It simplifies the OSI model into 4 layers.

## OSI vs TCP/IP Mapping

| OSI Layer        | TCP/IP Layer   | Function                          |
|------------------|---------------|-----------------------------------|
| 7,6,5 (App/Pres/Sess) | Application   | HTTP, FTP, DNS                    |
| 4 (Transport)    | Transport     | TCP, UDP                          |
| 3 (Network)      | Internet      | IP routing                        |
| 2,1 (Data/Physical) | Network Access | MAC, hardware                     |

---

## Encapsulation (How Data Moves)

- Data → Application  
- Segment → Transport (TCP/UDP added)  
- Packet → Internet (IP added)  
- Frame → Network Access (MAC added)  
- Bits → Physical signals  

---

## Important Protocols

- ARP – maps IP to MAC  
- DNS – converts domain to IP  
- DHCP – assigns IP automatically  
- ICMP – used for ping/troubleshooting  

---

## Layer 8 (Human Factor)

- User = weakest link  
- Example: phishing, social engineering  

